-- Canada Appoints Balsillie as Chairman of Clean Technology Agency
-- B y   G e r r i t   D e   V y n c k
-- 2013-06-25T14:11:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-25/canada-appoints-balsillie-as-chairman-of-clean-technology-agency.html
The Canadian government appointed
former BlackBerry co-chief executive officer  Jim Balsillie  as
chairman of a government agency that funds clean technologies.  Balsillie will serve as chairman of Sustainable Development
Technology Canada on a part-time basis for a five-year term,
Natural Resources Minister Joe Oliver said today in a release
from Toronto.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gerrit De Vynck in Toronto at 
 gdevynck@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
